body_text:
@suiyuan2009 Thanks for writing this!
It sounds like the problem you're trying to fix here is that the memory usage for zero-initializing variables is bigger than what it takes to store the variable. Is that it?
If so, I wonder if there's a better way of doing it than hacking scatter_add.

